item.title: Help with science
item.dc:creator: @Friday13th Friday13th
item.description:
@Friday13th wrote:

1: The human body has three pairs of salivary glands.
- true ( sublinguar, submandibular, parotical )
2: The function of the salivary enzyme is to aid in swallowing.
- false ( the salivary enzymes start to digastate shugar )
3: "Wisdom teeth" are more properly called molars.
- dont know how do you call them in english - the wisdom teeth are the last teeth to grow - we call them in poland -> Ã³semki -> the 8th. -> beause they are the 8th teeth
4: Incisors and canines are adapted for biting.
- what the hell inciors means ?? as for canines - true
5: Teeth are dead structures and have no blood supply.
- true - teeth are alive
6: Cavities in teeth may be enlarged by microorganisms.
- if bacteria is a microorganism then true
7: The diaphragm is located just below the stomach.
- false - its located over the stomach - just under the lungs
8: Stomach gland cells secrete gastric juice.
- true - they produce 3 enzymes ( dont know their names in english ) and HCl acid
9: A muscular valve at the end of the stomach controls the movement of food into the small intestine.
- true - its called gastro-duodenalis valve
10: Most of the chemical breakdown in digestion takes place in the stomach.
- false - the breakdown takes place in duodenum where enzymes from pancreas and liver start to act
11: The end-products of digestion are soluble in water.
- false
12: Liver bile contains a number of different digestive enzymes.
- false - bile is not an enzyme - to be exact it only helps to emulgate the fat in the duodenum
13: Fat digestion takes place in the pancreas.
- false - the pancreas produces enzymes + hormones - doesnt digastete. this process takes place in the duodenum
14: Alcohol may be absorbed by blood vessels in the stomach wall.
- false - rather because absorbation of water/alcohol doesnt take place in stomach - what would if be if You would be able to absorbe the HCl acid from the stomach ??
15: Glucose provides the main source of energy for body cells.
- false - the main surce of energy for the cell is ATP - adenozino three fosforan. The glucose is used to make the ATP, but its not a energy donor
16: The intestines are normally free of bacteria.
- false as hell - they are full of bacteria eg esherihia cloli
17: From ages twelve to sixteen, boys and girls need only about 1,000 Calories of food energy per day.
- rather true - but Im not sure of this one
18: Potatoes are much richer in proteins than is lean beef.
- false - potatoes contain saccharose
19: A good portion of the food eaten by the average American consists of indigestible material.
- who knows what you Americans eat ... ? I would rather say false - You just eat to mucth mcDonalds and other fast foods but its still digestible

Ok thats it I hope it will help
